{
  "texts": [
    "Then, we average these numbers.",
    "The average relative feature exclusion is over 99.6% for both classifiers over all counterfactual methods, and 99.8% if we include Anchors and SHAP.",
    "For many data sets, the average relative feature exclusion is even 100.0%.",
    "Meaning that for every instance that has to be explained, every feature of choice can be excluded from the explanation.",
    "These results show that it is fairly easy to avoid sensitive features in order to falsely justify model decisions."
  ]
}